02:42.155 --> 02:43.946
(radio announcer in background)
<i>A corrections spokesperson confirmed</i>

02:43.952 --> 02:46.858
<i>that two prisoners escaped via
a prison industry's workshop</i>

02:46.864 --> 02:49.598
<i>established by Regional
Manager, Derek Channing,</i>

02:49.604 --> 02:52.944
<i>who has been unavailable for
comment since the incident.</i>

02:52.950 --> 02:55.317
<i>Sources say Doyle and
Ferguson would've needed</i>

02:55.323 --> 02:58.205
<i>staff assistance to
orchestrate such an escape.</i>

02:58.211 --> 03:00.002
<i>The prison remains in lockdown,</i>

03:00.008 --> 03:03.322
<i>as investigators question
staff and inmates to establish</i>

03:03.328 --> 03:07.225
<i>if the two has assistance and what
their plans were on the outside.</i>

03:07.231 --> 03:11.170
<i>48 hours later, police remain on
the hunt for the Wentworth escapees.</i>

03:11.176 --> 03:13.111
<i>Earlier, a corrections
spokesperson...</i>

03:13.117 --> 03:15.708
<i>didn't think investigations
into that escape reflect</i>

03:15.714 --> 03:18.280
<i>on the integrity of the
prison security itself.</i>

03:18.286 --> 03:21.415
- <i>This week's escape, though, certainly does.</i>
- _

03:21.662 --> 03:24.967
<i>QUIBS have already questioned
around 100 inmates and staff</i>

03:24.973 --> 03:26.693
- <i>and intend to continue...</i>
- (siren wails)

03:27.266 --> 03:28.758
(tyres squealing)

03:28.764 --> 03:32.094
- (train horn sounds)
- (train crossing bells ringing)

03:33.400 --> 03:37.900
(train crossing bells continue)

03:40.572 --> 03:44.203
(male reporter) ...speak about
this at some point. It appears...

03:45.994 --> 03:47.995
- With both inmates still on the loose,
- ♪ (dark drumming music) ♪

03:48.001 --> 03:50.120
the prison and the
department are under pressure.

03:50.126 --> 03:53.512
Now, the Governor, Derek Channing,
has now been relieved from...

03:53.518 --> 03:54.789
(reporters clamouring)

03:54.795 --> 03:57.297
...Derek Channing has now
been relieved from his position

03:57.303 --> 04:00.078
and replaced by the former
Governor, Vera Bennett.

04:00.084 --> 04:01.777
She now faces the tough task

04:01.783 --> 04:04.987
- of trying to bring stability to her position...
- Move back.

04:06.578 --> 04:08.672
- WILL: Move back, please.
- REPORTER: Would you like to make a statement?

04:08.678 --> 04:09.972
Just move back, please!

04:12.489 --> 04:13.689
(cameras clicking and flashing)

04:13.695 --> 04:16.737
(flash warming up and camera clicking)

04:16.743 --> 04:19.743
♪ (dramatic music pulsating) ♪

04:21.902 --> 04:23.741
_

04:23.747 --> 04:26.747
♪ (music muffled) ♪

04:27.061 --> 04:29.420
_

04:29.426 --> 04:30.626
(silence)

04:30.937 --> 04:32.137
Name?

04:33.148 --> 04:34.348
Rita.

04:34.726 --> 04:35.926
Rita Connors.

04:35.932 --> 04:37.132
Date of birth?

04:37.322 --> 04:39.209
November, 15, '71.

04:39.215 --> 04:40.415
(keyboard clicking)

04:43.539 --> 04:44.862
Next of kin?

04:45.530 --> 04:46.730
Nuh.

04:50.954 --> 04:52.354
Can I keep my jacket?

04:53.048 --> 04:54.826
While you're on remand, yep.

04:55.409 --> 04:57.146
You'll need to lose the patches though.

04:59.506 --> 05:03.432
(siren wails)

05:05.198 --> 05:07.110
(door unlocks)

05:13.303 --> 05:14.996
- Press still out there?
- Yes...

05:15.002 --> 05:17.060
and the cops are back they
wanna speak to you again.

05:17.066 --> 05:18.587
Well, they have to wait.
What triggered the alarm?

05:18.593 --> 05:20.454
Ah, J Block set fire to some mattresses.

05:20.751 --> 05:22.768
- Fire brigade been called?
- It's okay, it's out.

05:23.018 --> 05:24.455
Slot them, slot the lot of them.

05:24.461 --> 05:27.041
Well, the slot's full. I mean, we
could separate the troublemakers,

05:27.047 --> 05:28.851
- put them in other blocks.
- Get onto it.

05:28.939 --> 05:30.252
Shut the hell up!

05:31.103 --> 05:34.103
- ♪ (melancholy music) ♪
- (siren continues wailing)

05:42.918 --> 05:45.918
- ♪♪
- (siren continues wailing)

05:48.907 --> 05:53.042
(inmates protesting in the background)

05:55.551 --> 05:59.237
(inmates protesting intensifies)

06:00.187 --> 06:01.387
(Boomer calls out, muffled)

06:03.574 --> 06:04.774
BOOMER: Hey!

06:04.882 --> 06:06.505
Can you let us outta here?

06:06.585 --> 06:09.108
'Cause it's not our fault
they fuckin' escaped, 'ey?

06:09.186 --> 06:12.355
- BOOMER: Just let us out.
- Mr Stewart... I need to talk to you.

06:12.356 --> 06:14.443
BOOMER: Hey, no one's
tellin' us nuffin' either.

06:14.449 --> 06:16.646
- How's Sonia, do you know?
- ALLIE: Mr Stewart...!

06:16.652 --> 06:18.063
- What's happening?
- BOOMER: Hey?!

06:18.069 --> 06:20.953
- Just keep moving, Connors.
- BOOMER: We want the tellies back on as well!

06:20.959 --> 06:22.329
Oh, come on!

06:22.335 --> 06:24.458
We're not fuckin' animals!

06:24.464 --> 06:25.664
(cell beeps unlocks)

06:25.670 --> 06:26.870
(siren continues wailing)

06:27.151 --> 06:29.346
The women are losing it.
I need to speak to the Governor.

06:29.352 --> 06:31.567
- Your cell's over there.
- You can't keep us cooped up like this.

06:31.573 --> 06:34.996
- It's a violation of our rights.
- Oh, really, is it? Welcome to prison.

06:35.517 --> 06:36.717
Oi?!

06:36.723 --> 06:37.923
(siren stops)

06:38.903 --> 06:40.103
You got a name?

06:40.376 --> 06:41.576
Rita.

06:41.582 --> 06:42.782
You a biker?

06:44.035 --> 06:45.235
Conquerors.

06:45.241 --> 06:46.681
You wanna be careful wearing that...

06:47.426 --> 06:50.123
someone in here might wanna
take it for themselves.

06:50.441 --> 06:51.738
They can try.

06:52.723 --> 06:54.463
I'm Kaz. I'm in charge around here.

06:54.636 --> 06:57.571
Remember that... we've got no problems.

07:02.120 --> 07:05.411
I am not making any statements.
Don't call this number again!

07:05.767 --> 07:07.266
- How'd they get your number?
- I don't know,

07:07.267 --> 07:09.007
but they know Channing's been fired.

07:09.268 --> 07:10.468
(door beeps unlocked)

07:10.580 --> 07:13.083
- (phone ringing)
- Sorry to keep you waiting.

07:13.089 --> 07:14.767
WILL: Um, I'll check on those transfers

07:14.898 --> 07:16.961
VERA: I thought you'd already
talked to all the women?

07:16.967 --> 07:18.854
We're following a new lead.

07:19.167 --> 07:22.471
We think Doyle and Ferguson had
help from your side of the bars.

07:22.477 --> 07:23.677
(door closes)

07:24.271 --> 07:26.582
We have a suspect we'd
like to talk to you about.

07:26.615 --> 07:27.815
Right, and who's that?

07:27.821 --> 07:30.482
Visitors' Centre records
show that Bridget Westfall

07:30.488 --> 07:33.713
visited Doyle three time in
the 10 days prior to her escape.

07:34.487 --> 07:38.290
Ms Westfall resigned some weeks
before, so why was she visiting Doyle?

07:38.478 --> 07:40.288
Well, you'd have to
ask Ms Westfall that.

07:40.470 --> 07:43.359
- If you're withholding any information...
- Look, I can't be certain...

07:43.618 --> 07:47.033
but it is possible that Doyle formed
some kind of emotional attachment.

07:47.696 --> 07:50.242
- Was it reciprocated?
- (phone ringing)

07:50.494 --> 07:52.328
- (phone continues ringing)
- I don't know.

07:52.777 --> 07:54.785
(phone ringing)

07:55.394 --> 07:56.894
I told you to hold my calls!

07:56.900 --> 07:58.605
Someone helped the
prisoners escape, Ms Bennett.

07:58.611 --> 08:00.973
- We need to establish who it was.
- (phone rings again)

08:02.317 --> 08:04.412
The sooner we recapture the escapees,

08:04.418 --> 08:06.225
the sooner your prison
returns to normal.

08:08.003 --> 08:09.630
WILL: Haven't got time
for this, Mitchell.

08:09.636 --> 08:10.836
Get off me! Nuh!

08:11.107 --> 08:13.513
- Move it, Mitchell! Come on!
- Not goin' anywhere! Nuh!

08:13.519 --> 08:14.826
I had nuffin' to do with it.

08:15.810 --> 08:18.209
- Not goin' nowhere. Can't hear me cloth ears?
- Let go.

08:18.215 --> 08:20.123
- I'm not goin' anywhere!
- What's goin' on, Mr Jackson?

08:20.129 --> 08:21.401
Nothing you need to worry about.

08:21.407 --> 08:25.098
- Last chance, Mitchell. Let's go.
- Treat us like animals and we'll act like one!

08:25.104 --> 08:26.789
Shut the fuck up!

08:26.795 --> 08:27.995
(Ruby chuckles)

08:28.001 --> 08:31.001
♪ (atmospheric music) ♪

08:33.724 --> 08:35.474
- (whooshing flourish)
- WILL: Let's go, Mitchell.

08:35.480 --> 08:37.513
You need to lift the lockdown!

08:43.017 --> 08:44.318
ALLIE: Miss Miles?

08:44.806 --> 08:47.615
Miss Miles, I need to
talk to Officer Stewart.

08:47.621 --> 08:48.920
I'll pop a note in his diary.

08:48.926 --> 08:50.126
Who the fuck's she?

08:50.132 --> 08:53.020
Trouble. Cell 16, play nice.

08:55.845 --> 08:57.045
What?

08:57.833 --> 09:00.119
Wasn't my fault.
Bitches trashed my unit.

09:00.125 --> 09:03.282
Hey, hey, hey. Hey, 16 not 15.

09:03.288 --> 09:05.399
All right, that's Franky's cell,
all right, you don't go in there.

09:05.405 --> 09:07.134
Okay? She's me best mate.

09:07.306 --> 09:09.931
- True. She's a legend.
- Yeah.

09:09.937 --> 09:12.013
I hope she gives those
pigs a run for their money.

09:12.917 --> 09:15.941
Hey, love, I haven't seen
you around. Are you a newbie?

09:15.947 --> 09:17.941
Nah, I've been over in
J Block for three months.

09:17.947 --> 09:19.710
- Got six left.
- BOOMER: Oh, yeah, what you in for?

09:19.716 --> 09:21.833
- For being black.
- (chuckles)

09:21.839 --> 09:23.639
Nah, for resisting arrest...

09:23.721 --> 09:25.338
but that's not my fault either.

09:25.651 --> 09:27.073
I'm seeing a pattern.

09:27.079 --> 09:29.455
Believe it or not, sugar tits.
(clicks mouth)

09:30.158 --> 09:31.358
(chuckles)

09:31.533 --> 09:34.666
Mmm, that's all we need, more attitude.

09:34.906 --> 09:37.906
- ♪ (atmospheric music) ♪
- (sighs)

09:43.829 --> 09:45.029
(sighs quietly)

09:52.540 --> 09:54.043
(muffled police sirens memory)

09:54.049 --> 09:56.865
(police sirens intensify)

