- (car decelerating in distance)
- (train horn sounds in distance)

10:38.061 --> 10:39.647
(radio in background)
<i>...Wentworth staff and prisoners alike.</i>

10:39.653 --> 10:41.725
<i>Given the apparent
conflict between the pair,</i>

10:41.731 --> 10:43.203
- <i>which reportedly dates back</i>
- WORKER: Pedro,

10:43.209 --> 10:44.623
- <i>to the appointment of Ferguson as</i>
- get your arse down here!

10:44.629 --> 10:45.943
<i>Wentworth's Governor.</i>

10:46.124 --> 10:48.634
- <i>One member of Wentworth's correctional staff,</i>
- PEDRO: All right.

10:48.640 --> 10:50.187
<i>who wished to remain unknown,</i>

10:50.193 --> 10:53.193
<i>said he "thought it was unlikely the
pair would be on the run together".</i>

10:53.664 --> 10:55.624
- <i>And now, a look at the weather.</i>
- (Franky sighs)

10:55.890 --> 10:58.288
- <i>Monko*, it's looking windy with showers.</i>
- ♪ (rhythmic tense music) ♪

10:58.294 --> 10:59.989
- <i>Forecast for Melbourne, partly cloudy</i>
- (Franky breathing heavily)

10:59.995 --> 11:02.372
<i>with a slight chance of
showers, mainly in the early...</i>

